---
import "../../styles/global.css";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <title>JD Navigation - Xi Lin</title>
  </head>
  <body class="bg-white text-gray-900">
    <main class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-16 sm:px-10">
      <a href="/" class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-500 hover:text-gray-900">Back to home</a>
      <h1 class="mt-6 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">Embodied Navigation Systems for Real-World Instruction Following</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600">
        At JD.com, I worked on embodied navigation systems spanning real-world VLN evaluation, VLM-based ObjectNav, zero-shot navigation, long-horizon planning, and model deployment for real robots.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-10 grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-2">
        <img src="/assets/projects/jd-robot-demo.png" alt="JD robot deployment" class="rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 object-cover" />
        <video controls playsinline class="w-full rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 bg-black">
          <source src="/assets/projects/jd-vln-demo.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
        </video>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-10 grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-2">
        <section class="rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 p-6">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">System Scope</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-gray-600">
            Covered evaluation, data collection, model training, finetuning, and deployment, with a focus on stable real-robot navigation in open environments.
          </p>
        </section>
        <section class="rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 p-6">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Research Direction</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-gray-600">
            This work led into MORN and world-model-related navigation reasoning, especially for long-horizon instruction following and embodied decision-making.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
